MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

2007-0767. State v. Jordan.

Trumbull App. No. 2006-T-0087, 2007-Ohio-1067. This cause is pending before the court as a discretionary appeal and claimed appeal of right. Upon consideration of appellee’s motion to strike the notice of appeal, memorandum in support of jurisdiction, affidavit of indigency, and case information statement,

It is ordered by the court that the motion is granted. Accordingly, this cause is dismissed.
